So the structure is like this.  Parent/Child1/main.py Parent/Child2/functions.py  I can't for the life of me, make main.py import functions from functions.py.  I've tried "from ..Parent.Child2.functions import *". I've tried "from .Child2.functions import *". These ones give me "ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'Parent'" and "ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'Child2'"  What am I doing wrong? Yes, I have tried "__init__.py" in every folder, no folder, only Child2 folder, only Parent and Child2 folders.
